# Coding Conventions

## Package Manager

- Use **pnpm 9.5.0** exclusively
- Run `pnpm install` before development
- Use `pnpm install --no-frozen-lockfile` only when updating dependencies

## Code Formatting & Linting

- **ESLint 9** (flat config) — each package has its own `eslint.config.mjs`
- Plugins: `typescript-eslint`, `import-x`, `jsx-a11y`, `react`, `react-hooks`, `i18next`, `unused-imports`, `@next/eslint-plugin-next`, `jsdoc`
- **Prettier** via `eslint-plugin-prettier` integration
- lint-staged runs on pre-commit

### Commands

```bash
pnpm lint          # lint all packages (via Turbo)
pnpm lint:fix      # auto-fix lint errors
pnpm build         # build all packages
pnpm dev           # start Next.js dev server
```

## Naming Conventions

| Element | Convention | Example |
|---------|-----------|---------|
| Package scope (this repo) | `@liberfi/` | `@liberfi/core`, `@liberfi/ui-dex` |
| Package scope (SDK) | `@liberfi.io/` | `@liberfi.io/client`, `@liberfi.io/ui-trade` |
| Component | PascalCase | `TokenListWidget` |
| Hook | `useXxx` | `useDexClient` |
| Route group | `(name)` | `(new)`, `(legacy)` |
| Page file | `page.tsx` | Next.js App Router convention |
| Layout file | `layout.tsx` | Next.js App Router convention |

## Comments

- All code comments MUST be written in **English** (see `english-comments.mdc`)
- Use JSDoc for public API functions and components

## Dependencies

### Adding @liberfi.io/* packages

When updating `@liberfi.io/*` versions:

1. Update `apps/web/package.json`
2. Update ALL `packages/*/package.json` (both `peerDependencies` and `devDependencies`)
3. Sync `@chainstream-io/sdk` version to match `@liberfi.io/client`'s dependency
4. **Stop here** — tell the user to run the following themselves:
   ```bash
   nrm use npm && pnpm install --no-frozen-lockfile && pnpm build && nrm use taobao
   ```

See `.cursor/rules/liberfi-sdk-context.mdc` for full rules.

### Singleton dependencies

These must use webpack alias in `next.config.mjs` to guarantee a single instance:

- `jotai`
- `@liberfi.io/ui-chain-select`
- Any package holding React Context or global state

## Environment Variables

- Prefix client-side vars with `NEXT_PUBLIC_`
- Define env vars in `turbo.json` → `globalEnv` / `env` for proper cache invalidation
- Never commit `.env.local`; reference `.env.example` for available variables
